headline: Humana (HUM): Profit Margins Decline Contradicts Optimistic Recovery Narratives
summary: Humana (HUM) reported net profit margins of 1.3%, down slightly from 1.5% a year ago. Earnings have trended negative over the past year and have declined by an average of 17.2% per year over the last five years. Looking ahead, analysts forecast a strong turnaround with earnings expected to grow 26.9% per year, well ahead of the broader US market's projected 15.8%. Revenue growth, however, is set to trail the overall market at 7.1% per year compared to 10.4%. With valuation multiples below...
